<D20Rules game-system="D&amp;D4E">

<!-- Version 1.00; May 2024 -->
<!-- Convert existing Born of Elements / Born of Shadow / Fey Bond feat chains into bloodlines. Also includes balance fixes to account for bloodlines being exclusive (and some feats were just terrible, like Child of Stone being worse than Toughness) -->
<!-- Added feats for the Elan Heritage bloodline themed around telepathy and mutual aid -->

<!-- Reworked Born of the Elements Feats -->
   <RulesElement name="Elemental Bloodline" type="Internal" internal-id="ID_INTERNAL_INTERNAL_ELEMENTAL_BLOODLINE" source="Core" >
   </RulesElement>

   <RulesElement name="Elemental Reversal" type="Power" internal-id="ID_FMP_POWER_HF_ELEM_BLOOD_1" source="HF Homebrew" revision-date="5/5/2024 9:36:42 AM" >
      <Category> ID_INTERNAL_CATEGORY_ENCOUNTER_USAGE,ID_FMP_CATEGORY_74,ID_INTERNAL_CATEGORY_IMMEDIATE_INTERRUPT </Category>
      <Flavor> You absorb elemental power intended to harm you, only to release it against your foes. </Flavor>
      <specific name="Power Usage"> Encounter </specific>
      <specific name="_SkillPower" />
      <specific name="Display"> Feat Power </specific>
      <specific name="Keywords"> Elemental </specific>
      <specific name="Action Type"> Immediate Interrupt </specific>
      <specific name="Attack Type"> Personal </specific>
      <specific name="Trigger"> You take acid, cold, fire, lightning, or thunder damage </specific>
      <specific name="Effect"> Reduce the triggering attack's damage by 5. The next attack you make before the end of your next turn deals an additional 5 damage of the same type which was prevented.
     Level 11: The amount of damage prevented and dealt increases to 10.
     Level 21: The amount of damage prevented and dealt increases to 15.</specific>
      <specific name="_Associated Feats" />
   </RulesElement>
	
	<RulesElement name="Born of the Elements" type="Feat" internal-id="ID_FMP_FEAT_3716" source="HF Homebrew" revision-date="5/5/2024 9:36:42 AM" >
		<Category> ID_INTERNAL_INTERNAL_ELEMENTAL_BLOODLINE </Category>
		<Prereqs> Humanoid; !bloodline or Elemental Bloodline</Prereqs>
		<print-prereqs> Humanoid </print-prereqs>
		<Flavor> Power flows up from the Elemental Chaos and through you, attuning your soul to its destructive energy. The influence of the Plane Below manifests itself in your preternatural resilience to environmental dangers. Furthermore, you have an instinctive knowledge of the elemental tongue and can communicate with creatures hailing from that plane. </Flavor>
		<specific name="Short Description"> Origin changes to elemental; strengthen elemental defenses; gain elemental reversal power </specific>
		<specific name="type"> Elemental Bloodline </specific>
		<specific name="Tier"> Heroic </specific>
		<specific name="_DisplayPowers"> ID_FMP_POWER_HF_ELEM_BLOOD_1 </specific>
		<rules>
			<drop name="ID_FMP_RACIAL_TRAIT_1139" type="Racial Trait"/>
			<drop name="ID_FMP_RACIAL_TRAIT_641" type="Racial Trait"/>
			<drop name="ID_FMP_RACIAL_TRAIT_1496" type="Racial Trait"/>
			<grant name="ID_TIV_RACIAL_TRAIT_ELEMENTAL_ORIGIN" type="Racial Trait"/>
			<grant name="ID_FMP_LANGUAGE_6" type="Language"/>
			<grant name="ID_FMP_POWER_HF_ELEM_BLOOD_1" type="Power"/>
			<statadd name="AC" value="+1" condition="against attacks with the acid, cold, fire, lightning, or thunder keywords" />
			<statadd name="Fortitude Defense" value="+1" condition="against attacks with the acid, cold, fire, lightning, or thunder keywords" />
			<statadd name="Reflex Defense" value="+1" condition="against attacks with the acid, cold, fire, lightning, or thunder keywords"/>
			<statadd name="Will Defense" value="+1" condition="against attacks with the acid, cold, fire, lightning, or thunder keywords"/>
			<grant name="ID_INTERNAL_INTERNAL_BLOODLINE" type="Internal"/>
			<grant name="ID_INTERNAL_INTERNAL_ELEMENTAL_BLOODLINE" type="Internal"/>
		</rules>
You can speak, read, and write Primordial. You gain a +1 bonus to all defenses against creatures with the air, earth, fire, or water keywords.
	In addition, you gain the elemental reversal power.
	</RulesElement>

	<RulesElement name="Child of Fire" type="Feat" internal-id="ID_FMP_FEAT_3718" source="HF Homebrew">
		<Category> ID_INTERNAL_INTERNAL_ELEMENTAL_BLOODLINE </Category>
		<Prereqs> Born of the Elements feat; !bloodline or Elemental Bloodline </Prereqs>
		<print-prereqs> Born of the Elements </print-prereqs>
		<Flavor> Elemental fire burns in your breast. These flames are eager to escape. Should your control ever slip, they rush free to scorch your foe. </Flavor>
		<specific name="Short Description"> Flames damage foe when you are bloodied or unconscious </specific>
	<specific name="type"> Elemental Bloodline </specific>
		<specific name="Tier"> Heroic </specific>
 	<rules>
	<grant name="ID_INTERNAL_INTERNAL_BLOODLINE" type="Internal"/>
	<grant name="ID_INTERNAL_INTERNAL_ELEMENTAL_BLOODLINE" type="Internal"/>
	</rules>
Whenever an attack bloodies you or knocks you unconscious, one enemy of your choice within 2 squares of you takes fire damage equal to your Constitution modifier.
	Level 11: One enemy within 3 squares.
	Level 21: All enemies within 5 squares.
	</RulesElement>
	<RulesElement name="Child of Stone" type="Feat" internal-id="ID_FMP_FEAT_3719" source="HF Homebrew">
		<Category> ID_INTERNAL_INTERNAL_ELEMENTAL_BLOODLINE </Category>
		<Prereqs> Born of the Elements feat; !bloodline or Elemental Bloodline </Prereqs>
		<print-prereqs> Born of the Elements </print-prereqs>
		<Flavor> You are a child of elemental earth; its power sustains and protects you. You can call forth earth's protective power to recover more swiftly when your need is greatest. </Flavor>
		<specific name="Short Description"> Use second wind as a move action </specific>
	<specific name="type"> Elemental Bloodline </specific>
		<specific name="Tier"> Heroic </specific>
 	<rules>
<modify name="Second Wind" field="Child of Stone" value="You can use your second wind as a move action."/>	
<grant name="ID_INTERNAL_INTERNAL_BLOODLINE" type="Internal"/>
	<grant name="ID_INTERNAL_INTERNAL_ELEMENTAL_BLOODLINE" type="Internal"/>
	</rules>
You can use your second wind as a move action.
	</RulesElement>
	<RulesElement name="Child of Storm" type="Feat" internal-id="ID_FMP_FEAT_3720" source="HF Homebrew">
		<Category> ID_INTERNAL_INTERNAL_ELEMENTAL_BLOODLINE </Category>
		<Prereqs> Born of the Elements feat; !bloodline or Elemental Bloodline</Prereqs>
		<print-prereqs> Born of the Elements </print-prereqs>
		<Flavor> The eldritch storms boiling across the Elemental Chaos reflect the turmoil in your heart. Elemental energy invigorates you. </Flavor>
		<specific name="Short Description"> +2 to next saving throw after taking elemental damage </specific>
	<specific name="type"> Elemental Bloodline </specific>
		<specific name="Tier"> Heroic </specific>
		<rules>
	<grant name="ID_INTERNAL_INTERNAL_BLOODLINE" type="Internal"/>
	<grant name="ID_INTERNAL_INTERNAL_ELEMENTAL_BLOODLINE" type="Internal"/>
			<statadd name="Saving Throws" value="+2" type="Feat" condition="after taking elemental damage"/>
		</rules>
Whenever you take acid, cold, fire, lightning, or thunder damage from an enemy attack, you gain a +2 bonus to your next saving throw during this encounter. This bonus stacks with itself.
	</RulesElement>
	<RulesElement name="Child of the Sea" type="Feat" internal-id="ID_FMP_FEAT_3721" source="HF Homebrew">
		<Category> ID_INTERNAL_INTERNAL_ELEMENTAL_BLOODLINE </Category>
		<Prereqs> Born of the Elements feat; !bloodline or Elemental Bloodline </Prereqs>
		<print-prereqs> Born of the Elements </print-prereqs>
		<Flavor> You are the most free when swimming. Your elemental heritage lets you maneuver through waters with ease as if you were born to it. </Flavor>
		<specific name="Short Description"> Gain swim speed, other aquatic benefits </specific>
	<specific name="type"> Elemental Bloodline </specific>
		<specific name="Tier"> Heroic </specific>
 	<rules>
	<grant name="ID_INTERNAL_INTERNAL_BLOODLINE" type="Internal"/>
	<grant name="ID_INTERNAL_INTERNAL_ELEMENTAL_BLOODLINE" type="Internal"/>
	</rules>
You have a swim speed equal to your walking speed. In addition, you count as having the aquatic keyword.
	</RulesElement>
	<RulesElement name="Child of Wind" type="Feat" internal-id="ID_FMP_FEAT_3722" source="HF Homebrew">
		<Category> ID_INTERNAL_INTERNAL_ELEMENTAL_BLOODLINE </Category>
		<Prereqs> Born of the Elements feat; !bloodline or Elemental Bloodline </Prereqs>
		<print-prereqs> Born of the Elements </print-prereqs>
		<Flavor> Drawing on your heritage of elemental air gives lift to your steps. </Flavor>
		<specific name="Short Description"> Ignore difficult terrain when not wearing heavy armor </specific>
	<specific name="type"> Elemental Bloodline </specific>
		<specific name="Tier"> Heroic </specific>
 	<rules>
	<grant name="ID_INTERNAL_INTERNAL_BLOODLINE" type="Internal"/>
	<grant name="ID_INTERNAL_INTERNAL_ELEMENTAL_BLOODLINE" type="Internal"/>
	</rules>
Whenever you are not wearing heavy armor, you ignore difficult terrain.
	</RulesElement>
	<RulesElement name="Earthwalker" type="Feat" internal-id="ID_FMP_FEAT_3723" source="HF Homebrew">
		<Category> ID_INTERNAL_INTERNAL_ELEMENTAL_BLOODLINE </Category>
		<Prereqs> Born of the Elements feat; !bloodline or Elemental Bloodline </Prereqs>
		<print-prereqs> Born of the Elements </print-prereqs>
		<Flavor> Your elemental heritage manifests as an affinity for elemental earth. Neither rubble nor uneven stone hampers you, for you can call upon your heritage to let you move through solid rock. </Flavor>
		<specific name="Short Description"> Gain earth walk; gain phasing after using second wind </specific>
	<specific name="type"> Elemental Bloodline </specific>
		<specific name="Tier"> Heroic </specific>
		<rules>
	<grant name="ID_INTERNAL_INTERNAL_BLOODLINE" type="Internal"/>
	<grant name="ID_INTERNAL_INTERNAL_ELEMENTAL_BLOODLINE" type="Internal"/>
			<modify name="Second Wind" field="Earthwalker" value="Whenever you use your second wind, you have phasing until the end of your next turn. Using this feat, you can phase only through earth and rock."/>
		</rules>
You gain earth walk, meaning that you ignore difficult terrain caused by rubble, uneven stone, or earthen construction.
	In addition, whenever you use your second wind, you have phasing until the end of your next turn. Using this feat, you can phase only through earth and rock.
	</RulesElement>
	<RulesElement name="Firedancer" type="Feat" internal-id="ID_FMP_FEAT_3729" source="HF Homebrew">
		<Category> ID_INTERNAL_INTERNAL_ELEMENTAL_BLOODLINE </Category>
		<Prereqs> Born of the Elements feat; !bloodline or Elemental Bloodline </Prereqs>
		<print-prereqs> Born of the Elements </print-prereqs>
		<Flavor> You have a connection to elemental fire thanks to your elemental heritage. You do not fear flames since they no longer burn you. </Flavor>
		<specific name="Short Description"> Gain resist 5/10/15 fire; deal fire damage after using second wind </specific>
	<specific name="type"> Elemental Bloodline </specific>
		<specific name="Tier"> Heroic </specific>
		<rules>
			<statadd name="resist:fire" value="+5" type="resist" zero="true"/>
			<statadd name="resist:fire" value="+5" type="resist" non-zero="true"/>
			<statadd name="resist:fire" value="+5" type="resist" requires="11 level" zero="true"/>
			<statadd name="resist:fire" value="+5" type="resist" requires="11 level" non-zero="true"/>
			<statadd name="resist:fire" value="+5" type="resist" requires="21 level" zero="true"/>
			<statadd name="resist:fire" value="+5" type="resist" requires="21 level" non-zero="true"/>
			<modify name="Second Wind" field="Firedancer" value="When you use your second wind, your melee and ranged attacks deal 1d6 extra fire damage until the end of your next turn."/>
	<grant name="ID_INTERNAL_INTERNAL_BLOODLINE" type="Internal"/>
	<grant name="ID_INTERNAL_INTERNAL_ELEMENTAL_BLOODLINE" type="Internal"/>
		</rules>
You gain resist 5 fire. This resistance increases to 10 at 11th level and 15 at 21st level. If you already have fire resistance, it instead increases by 5.
	In addition, when you use your second wind, your melee and ranged attacks deal 1d6 extra fire damage until the end of your next turn.
	</RulesElement>
	<RulesElement name="Rising Chaos" type="Feat" internal-id="ID_FMP_FEAT_3733" source="HF Homebrew">
		<Category> ID_INTERNAL_INTERNAL_ELEMENTAL_BLOODLINE </Category>
		<Prereqs> Born of the Elements feat; !bloodline or Elemental Bloodline </Prereqs>
		<print-prereqs> Born of the Elements </print-prereqs>
		<Flavor> You feel new strength awaken within you whenever you must confront elemental energy. The power awakened bolsters your attacks. </Flavor>
		<specific name="Short Description"> +2 to damage rolls after using elemental absorption </specific>
	<specific name="type"> Elemental Bloodline </specific>
		<specific name="Tier"> Heroic </specific>
		<rules>
			<statadd name="damage rolls" value="+2" type="feat" condition="after using elemental absorption."/>
	<grant name="ID_INTERNAL_INTERNAL_BLOODLINE" type="Internal"/>
	<grant name="ID_INTERNAL_INTERNAL_ELEMENTAL_BLOODLINE" type="Internal"/>
		</rules>
After you use your elemental absorption power, you gain a +2 bonus to damage rolls until the end of the encounter.
	</RulesElement>
	<RulesElement name="Seastrider" type="Feat" internal-id="ID_FMP_FEAT_3734" source="HF Homebrew">
		<Category> ID_INTERNAL_INTERNAL_ELEMENTAL_BLOODLINE </Category>
		<Prereqs> 21st level, Born of the Elements feat; !bloodline or Elemental Bloodline </Prereqs>
		<print-prereqs> 21st level, Born of the Elements </print-prereqs>
		<Flavor> Your elemental heritage manifests as an affinity for elemental water. You can use elemental water's power to flow through your enemies and across liquid surfaces. </Flavor>
		<specific name="Short Description"> Shift through enemies' spaces, move across liquid </specific>
	<specific name="type"> Elemental Bloodline </specific>
		<specific name="Tier"> Epic </specific>
 	<rules>
	<grant name="ID_INTERNAL_INTERNAL_BLOODLINE" type="Internal"/>
	<grant name="ID_INTERNAL_INTERNAL_ELEMENTAL_BLOODLINE" type="Internal"/>
	</rules>
You can shift through enemies' spaces.
	In addition, when you move, you may treat liquid surfaces as though they were solid ground. If you end the move on the liquid, you sink.
	</RulesElement>
	<RulesElement name="Windfoot" type="Feat" internal-id="ID_FMP_FEAT_3737" source="Heroes of the Elemental Chaos">
		<Category> ID_INTERNAL_INTERNAL_ELEMENTAL_BLOODLINE </Category>
		<Prereqs> 21st level, Born of the Elements feat </Prereqs>
		<print-prereqs> 21st level, Born of the Elements </print-prereqs>
		<Flavor> You have an affinity for elemental air thanks to your unusual heritage. </Flavor>
		<specific name="Short Description"> Take no damage from falling; fly after using second wind </specific>
	<specific name="type"> Elemental Bloodline </specific>
		<specific name="Tier"> Epic </specific>
		<rules>
	<grant name="ID_INTERNAL_INTERNAL_BLOODLINE" type="Internal"/>
	<grant name="ID_INTERNAL_INTERNAL_ELEMENTAL_BLOODLINE" type="Internal"/>
			<modify name="Second Wind" field="Windfoot" value="When you use your second wind, you can fly up to your speed as a free action."/>
		</rules>
You take no damage from falling.
	In addition, when you use your second wind, you can fly up to your speed as a free action.
	</RulesElement>

	<RulesElement name="Elemental Companion" type="Feat" internal-id="ID_FMP_FEAT_3724" source="HF Homebrew">
		<Category> ID_FMP_FEAT_3724 </Category>
		<Prereqs> Elemental origin, !ID_FMP_FEAT_738 </Prereqs>
		<print-prereqs> Elemental origin, must not have the Arcane Familiar feat </print-prereqs>
		<Flavor> You fashion a companion from raw elemental substance. The companion aids you in your endeavors when called. (See page 146 of Heroes of Elemental Chaos for a selection of elemental companions.) </Flavor>
		<specific name="Short Description"> You gain an elemental companion </specific>
		<specific name="Type"> Elemental Companion </specific>
		<specific name="Tier"> Heroic </specific>
		<specific name="_PARSED_SUB_FEATURES"> ID_INTERNAL_CLASS_FEATURE_ELEMENTAL_COMPANION_(ARCTINE),ID_INTERNAL_CLASS_FEATURE_ELEMENTAL_COMPANION_(AUTOMATON),ID_INTERNAL_CLASS_FEATURE_ELEMENTAL_COMPANION_(CHAOS_PHAGE),ID_INTERNAL_CLASS_FEATURE_ELEMENTAL_COMPANION_(CRYSMALITE),ID_INTERNAL_CLASS_FEATURE_ELEMENTAL_COMPANION_(FLAME_SERPENT),ID_INTERNAL_CLASS_FEATURE_ELEMENTAL_COMPANION_(HORDELING),ID_INTERNAL_CLASS_FEATURE_ELEMENTAL_COMPANION_(MUD_WRENCH),ID_INTERNAL_CLASS_FEATURE_ELEMENTAL_COMPANION_(MAGMIN),ID_INTERNAL_CLASS_FEATURE_ELEMENTAL_COMPANION_(NEREID),ID_INTERNAL_CLASS_FEATURE_ELEMENTAL_COMPANION_(PECH),ID_INTERNAL_CLASS_FEATURE_ELEMENTAL_COMPANION_(STORM_TALON),ID_INTERNAL_CLASS_FEATURE_ELEMENTAL_COMPANION_(SYLPH) </specific>
		<specific name="_DisplayPowers"/>
		<rules>
			<select type="Class Feature" number="1" Category="ID_FMP_FEAT_3724"/>
Choose Elemental Companion
		</rules>
You gain an elemental companion.
	For each elemental companion feat you have beyond this one, your elemental companion gains a +1 bonus to all defenses.
	</RulesElement>

