<RulesElement name="Shadow Blood" type="Feat" internal-id="ID_FMP_FEAT_3569" source="HF Homebrew" revision-date="3/10/2011 12:45:12 PM">
      <Category> ID_INTERNAL_INTERNAL_SHADOW_BLOODLINE </Category>
		<Prereqs> Born of Shadow; !bloodline or Shadow Bloodline </Prereqs>
		<print-prereqs> Born of Shadow </print-prereqs>
		<Flavor> Although others feel the chill of fear in the shadows, you find only solace in the darkness. When you draw on your inner reserves of strength, the shadow that cloaks you grants you even more vitality. </Flavor>
		<specific name="Tier"> Heroic </specific>
		<specific name="Short Description"> Regain +5/+10/+15 (by tier) hp while not in bright light </specific>
		<specific name="Special"/>
	        <specific name="type"> Shadow Bloodline </specific>
		<specific name="Associated Power Info"/>
		<specific name="Associated Powers"/>
      <rules>
	<grant name="ID_INTERNAL_INTERNAL_BLOODLINE" type="Internal"/>
	<grant name="ID_INTERNAL_INTERNAL_SHADOW_BLOODLINE" type="Internal"/>
	<modify name="Second Wind" field="Shadow Blood" value="When in dim light or darkness, regain an additional 5/10/15 hit points."/>
      </rules>
When you are the target of a healing power or use your second wind to regain hit points while you are in dim light or darkness, you regain 5 additional hit points. The additional hit points increase to 10 at 11th level and 15 at 21st level.
	</RulesElement>

	<RulesElement name="Shadow Control" type="Feat" internal-id="ID_FMP_FEAT_3570" source="HF Homebrew" revision-date="3/10/2011 12:45:14 PM">
      <Category> ID_INTERNAL_INTERNAL_SHADOW_BLOODLINE </Category>
		<Prereqs> Born of Shadow; !bloodline or Shadow Bloodline </Prereqs>
		<print-prereqs> Born of Shadow </print-prereqs>
		<Flavor> The shadow magic you channel lets you summon strength from the darkness, drawing down shadows that shift and swirl to shield you from attacks. </Flavor>
		<specific name="Tier"> Heroic </specific>
		<specific name="Short Description"> +1 to defenses while not in bright light </specific>
		<specific name="Special"/>
  	        <specific name="type"> Shadow Bloodline </specific>
		<specific name="Associated Power Info"/>
		<specific name="Associated Powers"/>
		<rules>
			<statadd name="AC" value="+1" condition="while you are in dim light or darkness"/>
			<statadd name="Fortitude Defense" value="+1" condition="while you are in dim light or darkness"/>
			<statadd name="Reflex Defense" value="+1" condition="while you are in dim light or darkness"/>
			<statadd name="Will Defense" value="+1" condition="while you are in dim light or darkness"/>
			<grant name="ID_INTERNAL_INTERNAL_BLOODLINE" type="Internal"/>
                 	<grant name="ID_INTERNAL_INTERNAL_SHADOW_BLOODLINE" type="Internal"/>
		</rules>
You gain a +1 bonus to all defenses while you are in dim light or darkness.
	</RulesElement>

	<RulesElement name="Shadow Mantle" type="Feat" internal-id="ID_FMP_FEAT_3571" source="HF Homebrew" revision-date="3/10/2011 12:45:16 PM">
      <Category> ID_INTERNAL_INTERNAL_SHADOW_BLOODLINE </Category>
		<Prereqs> Born of Shadow; !bloodline or Shadow Bloodline </Prereqs>
		<print-prereqs> Born of Shadow </print-prereqs>
		<Flavor> At the height of combat, shadow flares to accentuate your movements, then conceals you as you execute your next assault. </Flavor>
		<specific name="Tier"> Heroic </specific>
		<specific name="Short Description"> Gain concealment until EoNT when you crit or drop nonminion enemy </specific>
		<specific name="Special"/>
         	<specific name="type"> Shadow Bloodline </specific>
		<specific name="Associated Power Info"/>
		<specific name="Associated Powers"/>
		<rules>
	<grant name="ID_INTERNAL_INTERNAL_BLOODLINE" type="Internal"/>
	<grant name="ID_INTERNAL_INTERNAL_SHADOW_BLOODLINE" type="Internal"/>
		</rules>
When you score a critical hit or reduce a nonminion enemy to 0 hit points, you gain partial concealment until the end of your next turn.
	</RulesElement>

	<RulesElement name="Shadow Overflow" type="Feat" internal-id="ID_FMP_FEAT_3572" source="HF Homebrew" revision-date="3/10/2011 12:45:17 PM">
      <Category> ID_INTERNAL_INTERNAL_SHADOW_BLOODLINE </Category>
		<Prereqs> Born of Shadow; !bloodline or Shadow Bloodline </Prereqs>
		<print-prereqs> Born of Shadow </print-prereqs>
		<Flavor> Your soul is imbued with shadow energy that flows through your attacks. Each time you slay an enemy, tendrils of that shadow lash out against your other foes. </Flavor>
		<specific name="Tier"> Heroic </specific>
		<specific name="Short Description"> Enemy within 2/3/5 sq. takes Con modifier necrotic damage when you drop nonminion enemy </specific>
		<specific name="Special"/>
      <specific name="type"> Shadow Bloodline </specific>
		<specific name="Associated Power Info"/>
		<specific name="Associated Powers"/>
		<rules>
	<grant name="ID_INTERNAL_INTERNAL_BLOODLINE" type="Internal"/>
	<grant name="ID_INTERNAL_INTERNAL_SHADOW_BLOODLINE" type="Internal"/>
		</rules>
Whenever you reduce a nonminion enemy to 0 hit points, one enemy within 2 squares of you takes necrotic damage equal to your Constitution modifier.
     Level 11: One enemy within 3 squares of you.
     Level 21: All enemies within 5 squares of you.
	</RulesElement>

	<RulesElement name="Shadow Strider" type="Feat" internal-id="ID_FMP_FEAT_3573" source="HF Homebrew" revision-date="3/10/2011 12:45:19 PM">
      <Category> ID_INTERNAL_INTERNAL_SHADOW_BLOODLINE </Category>
		<Prereqs> Born of Shadow; !bloodline or Shadow Bloodline </Prereqs>
		<print-prereqs> Born of Shadow </print-prereqs>
		<Flavor> As a creature of shadow, you move through the night with ease. Darkness coalesces around you, making it easy to pick your way through even the roughest terrain. </Flavor>
		<specific name="Tier"> Heroic </specific>
		<specific name="Short Description"> Ignore difficult terrain in squares of dim light or darkness </specific>
		<specific name="Special"/>
      <specific name="type"> Shadow Bloodline </specific>
		<specific name="Associated Power Info"/>
		<specific name="Associated Powers"/>
		<rules>
	<grant name="ID_INTERNAL_INTERNAL_BLOODLINE" type="Internal"/>
	<grant name="ID_INTERNAL_INTERNAL_SHADOW_BLOODLINE" type="Internal"/>
		</rules>
You ignore difficult terrain in squares of dim light or darkness.
	</RulesElement>

<!-- Fey Bond bloodline conversion -->
<!-- Also includes other "fey"-themed feats which are not race-specific -->
<!-- This bloodline was reworked more than the other two, as there were only three generic "fey" feats in Heroes of the Feywild and the older Dragon feats overlapped one another considerably -->

<RulesElement name="Fey Bloodline" type="Internal" internal-id="ID_INTERNAL_INTERNAL_FEY_BLOODLINE" source="Core" >
   </RulesElement>

	<RulesElement name="Fey Bond" type="Feat" internal-id="ID_FMP_FEAT_3652" source="Heroes of the Feywild">
             	<Category> ID_INTERNAL_INTERNAL_FEY_BLOODLINE </Category>
		<Prereqs> Humanoid; !bloodline or Fey Bloodline </Prereqs>
		<print-prereqs> Humanoid </print-prereqs>
		<Flavor> Through your knowledge and experience of the fey, you have acquired some of their qualities, perhaps as a reward from the Feywild's archfey, and you have learned the language of the elves and their kin. </Flavor>
		<specific name="Short Description"> Origin changes to fey; gain Elven (or Goblin/Giant), +2 to Bluff and Diplomacy checks </specific>
		<specific name="Tier"> Heroic </specific>
	        <specific name="type"> Fey Bloodline </specific>
		<rules>
			<drop name="ID_FMP_RACIAL_TRAIT_1139" type="Racial Trait"/>
			<drop name="ID_FMP_RACIAL_TRAIT_519" type="Racial Trait"/>
			<drop name="ID_FMP_RACIAL_TRAIT_1496" type="Racial Trait"/>
			<grant name="ID_FMP_RACIAL_TRAIT_641" type="Racial Trait"/>
			<statadd name="Bluff Racial" value="+2"/>
			<statadd name="Diplomacy Racial" value="+2"/>
			<select type="Language" number="1" Category="ID_FMP_LANGUAGE_4|ID_FMP_LANGUAGE_19|ID_FMP_LANGUAGE_20" default="ID_FMP_LANGUAGE_4"/>
			<grant name="ID_INTERNAL_INTERNAL_BLOODLINE" type="Internal"/>
			<grant name="ID_INTERNAL_INTERNAL_FEY_BLOODLINE" type="Internal"/>
		</rules>
Your origin becomes fey and you gain a +2 racial bonus to Bluff checks and Diplomacy checks.
	In addition, you can speak, read, and write Elven. (If you already know Elven, you can choose Giant or Goblin instead.)
	</RulesElement>

	<RulesElement name="Fey Cantrip" type="Feat" internal-id="ID_FMP_FEAT_3653" source="Heroes of the Feywild">
      <Category> ID_INTERNAL_INTERNAL_FEY_BLOODLINE </Category>
		<Prereqs> Fey Bond; !bloodline or Fey Bloodline </Prereqs>
		<print-prereqs> Fey Bond </print-prereqs>
		<Flavor> You have picked up a magic trick as a result of your connection to the Feywild. </Flavor>
		<specific name="Short Description"> Gain a cantrip </specific>
		<specific name="Tier"> Heroic </specific>
	        <specific name="type"> Fey Bloodline </specific>
		<rules>
			<modify name="ID_FMP_POWER_12731" type="Power" Field="Power Type" value="Utility"/>
			<modify name="ID_FMP_POWER_1217" type="Power" Field="Power Type" value="Utility"/>
			<modify name="ID_FMP_POWER_1225" type="Power" Field="Power Type" value="Utility"/>
			<modify name="ID_FMP_POWER_1227" type="Power" Field="Power Type" value="Utility"/>
			<modify name="ID_FMP_POWER_1930" type="Power" Field="Power Type" value="Utility"/>
			<modify name="ID_FMP_POWER_13970" type="Power" Field="Power Type" value="Utility"/>
			<modify name="ID_FMP_POWER_13971" type="Power" Field="Power Type" value="Utility"/>
			<select type="Power" number="1" Category="ID_FMP_CLASS_FEATURE_2870"/>
			<grant name="ID_INTERNAL_INTERNAL_BLOODLINE" type="Internal"/>
			<grant name="ID_INTERNAL_INTERNAL_FEY_BLOODLINE" type="Internal"/>
		</rules>
Choose one wizard cantrip, such as mage hand or prestidigitation. You gain that power.
	</RulesElement>

	<RulesElement name="Fey Companions" type="Feat" internal-id="ID_FMP_FEAT_3509" source="Dragon Magazine 392" revision-date="12/06/2010 11:37:44 AM">
      <Category> ID_INTERNAL_INTERNAL_FEY_BLOODLINE </Category>
		<Prereqs> Fey Bond; !bloodline or Fey Bloodline </Prereqs>
		<print-prereqs> Fey Bond </print-prereqs>
		<specific name="Short Description"> Gain a fey-themed familiar </specific>
		<specific name="Tier"> Heroic </specific>
		<specific name="Special"/>
	        <specific name="type"> Fey Bloodline </specific>
		<specific name="Associated Power Info"/>
		<specific name="Associated Powers"/>
		<rules>
			<select type="Familiar" number="1" Category="ID_FMP_FAMILIAR_89|ID_FMP_FAMILIAR_31|ID_FMP_FAMILIAR_88|ID_FMP_FAMILIAR_88|ID_FMP_FAMILIAR_82|ID_FMP_FAMILIAR_79|ID_FMP_FAMILIAR_102|ID_FMP_FAMILIAR_37|ID_FMP_FAMILIAR_76" />
			<grant name="ID_INTERNAL_INTERNAL_BLOODLINE" type="Internal"/>
			<grant name="ID_INTERNAL_INTERNAL_FEY_BLOODLINE" type="Internal"/>
		</rules>
	  You gain a fey-themed familiar, which gains a +1 bonus to all defenses for every other Fey Bloodline feat which you have.
	</RulesElement>

	<RulesElement name="Fey Senses" type="Feat" internal-id="ID_FMP_FEAT_2727" source="Dragon Magazine 384" revision-date="8/27/2010 12:20:34 PM">
      <Category> ID_INTERNAL_INTERNAL_FEY_BLOODLINE </Category>
		<Prereqs> Fey Bond; !bloodline or Fey Bloodline </Prereqs>
		<print-prereqs> Fey Bond </print-prereqs>
		<specific name="Tier"> Heroic </specific>
		<specific name="Short Description"> +2 to Perception and Insight, sense magic with Perception </specific>
		<specific name="Special"/>
	        <specific name="type"> Fey Bloodline </specific>
		<specific name="Associated Power Info"/>
		<specific name="Associated Powers"/>
		<rules>
			<statadd name="Perception Misc" value="+2" type="Feat"/>
			<statadd name="Insight Misc" value="+2" type="Feat"/>
			<grant name="ID_INTERNAL_INTERNAL_BLOODLINE" type="Internal"/>
			<grant name="ID_INTERNAL_INTERNAL_FEY_BLOODLINE" type="Internal"/>
		</rules>
You gain a +2 feat bonus to Perception and Insight. In addition, you can use Perception in place of Arcana to sense the presence of magic.
	</RulesElement>

	<RulesElement name="Fey-Minded" type="Feat" internal-id="ID_FMP_FEAT_2728" source="Dragon Magazine 384" revision-date="8/27/2010 12:20:34 PM">
      <Category> ID_INTERNAL_INTERNAL_FEY_BLOODLINE </Category>
		<Prereqs> Fey Bond; !bloodline or Fey Bloodline </Prereqs>
		<print-prereqs> Fey Bond </print-prereqs>
		<specific name="Tier"> Heroic </specific>
		<specific name="Short Description"> Use Nature instead of Arcana for fey monster knowledge, saving throw against charm at start of turn </specific>
		<specific name="Special"/>
	        <specific name="type"> Fey Bloodline </specific>
		<specific name="Associated Power Info"/>
		<specific name="Associated Powers"/>
		<rules>	
			<grant name="ID_INTERNAL_INTERNAL_BLOODLINE" type="Internal"/>
			<grant name="ID_INTERNAL_INTERNAL_FEY_BLOODLINE" type="Internal"/>
</rules>
You can use Nature in place of Arcana for fey-related monster knowledge checks. At the start of your turn, you can make a saving throw against a charm effect that a save could end. On a save, the effect immediately ends.
	</RulesElement>

	<RulesElement name="Fey Shift" type="Feat" internal-id="ID_FMP_FEAT_3655" source="Heroes of the Feywild">
      <Category> ID_INTERNAL_INTERNAL_FEY_BLOODLINE </Category>
		<Prereqs> 21st level, Fey Bond; !bloodline or Fey Bloodline </Prereqs>
		<print-prereqs> 21st level, Fey Bond </print-prereqs>
		<Flavor> Harnessing a power that is innate to many Feywild creatures, you can step through planar shortcuts, albeit only for short distances. </Flavor>
		<specific name="Short Description"> Teleport 2 squares as move action </specific>
		<specific name="Tier"> Epic </specific>
	        <specific name="type"> Fey Bloodline </specific>
		<rules>	
			<grant name="ID_INTERNAL_INTERNAL_BLOODLINE" type="Internal"/>
			<grant name="ID_INTERNAL_INTERNAL_FEY_BLOODLINE" type="Internal"/>
</rules>
You can teleport up to 2 squares as a move action.
	</RulesElement>

<!-- Additional Elan feat, based on Psionic Incarnate feature -->

	<RulesElement name="Psionic Repletion" type="Feat" internal-id="ID_FMP_FEAT_HF_ELAN_1" source="HF Homebrew">
      <Category> ID_INTERNAL_INTERNAL_ELAN_BLOODLINE </Category>
		<Prereqs> Elan Heritage; !bloodline or Elan Bloodline </Prereqs>
		<print-prereqs> Elan Heritage </print-prereqs>
		<Flavor> You have found a way to allow psionic energy to sustain your form. </Flavor>
		<specific name="Short Description"> +2 Endurance, no need to eat or breathe, rest quickly </specific>
		<specific name="Tier"> Heroic </specific>
	        <specific name="type"> Elan Bloodline </specific>
		<rules>	
			<statadd name="Endurance Misc" value="+2" type="Feat"/>			
			<grant name="ID_INTERNAL_INTERNAL_BLOODLINE" type="Internal"/>
			<grant name="ID_INTERNAL_INTERNAL_ELAN_BLOODLINE" type="Internal"/>
</rules>
You gain a +2 feat bonus to Endurance checks. You no longer need to breathe, eat, or drink. In addition, you do not sleep and instead enter a state of dormancy in which you remain fully aware of your surroundings. You only need four hours in this state to gain the same benefits other races gain from taking a 6-hour extended rest.
	</RulesElement>

<!-- Additional Elan feats, based on enhancing Elan telepathy along the theme of "assistance" -->

	<RulesElement name="Telepathic Assistance" type="Feat" internal-id="ID_FMP_FEAT_HF_ELAN_2" source="HF Homebrew">
      <Category> ID_INTERNAL_INTERNAL_ELAN_BLOODLINE </Category>
		<Prereqs> Elan Heritage; !bloodline or Elan Bloodline </Prereqs>
		<print-prereqs> Elan Heritage </print-prereqs>
		<Flavor> You can be the helpful voice in someone's head. </Flavor>
		<specific name="Short Description"> Aid another within range of telepathy/as minor action </specific>
		<specific name="Tier"> Heroic </specific>
	        <specific name="type"> Elan Bloodline </specific>
		<rules>		
			<grant name="ID_INTERNAL_INTERNAL_BLOODLINE" type="Internal"/>
			<grant name="ID_INTERNAL_INTERNAL_ELAN_BLOODLINE" type="Internal"/>
</rules>
You do not need to be adjacent to a creature when using the aid another action so long as it is within range of your telepathy. You may also choose to use a minor action to take the aid another action rather than a standard action, but if you fail, the target takes a -2 penalty to the next check due to the distraction.
	</RulesElement>

	<RulesElement name="Nascent Hive Mind" type="Feat" internal-id="ID_FMP_FEAT_HF_ELAN_3" source="HF Homebrew">
      <Category> ID_INTERNAL_INTERNAL_ELAN_BLOODLINE </Category>
		<Prereqs> 21st level, Elan Heritage; !bloodline or Elan Bloodline </Prereqs>
		<print-prereqs> 21st level, Elan Heritage </print-prereqs>
		<Flavor> You connect your allies in a mental web, allowing you to support one another's minds from a distance. </Flavor>
		<specific name="Short Description"> Telepathy 10; aid another within range of telepathy/as free action for mental checks </specific>
		<specific name="Tier"> Epic </specific>
	        <specific name="type"> Elan Bloodline </specific>
		<rules>		
			<grant name="ID_INTERNAL_INTERNAL_BLOODLINE" type="Internal"/>
			<grant name="ID_INTERNAL_INTERNAL_ELAN_BLOODLINE" type="Internal"/>
</rules>
The range of your telepathy increases to 10. When you or an ally within range of your telepathy makes an Intelligence-based, Wisdom-based, or Charisma-based ability check or skill check, up to four of you within range of your telepathy may take the aid another action as a free action to assist with that check (they need not be adjacent to the target being assisted).
	</RulesElement>

<!-- Additional Elan feat, based on enhancing Elan telepathy to improve distance/line of effect concerns -->

	<RulesElement name="Improved Telepathic Connection" type="Feat" internal-id="ID_FMP_FEAT_HF_ELAN_4" source="HF Homebrew">
      <Category> ID_INTERNAL_INTERNAL_ELAN_BLOODLINE </Category>
		<Prereqs> 11th level, Elan Heritage; !bloodline or Elan Bloodline </Prereqs>
		<print-prereqs> 11th level, Elan Heritage </print-prereqs>
		<Flavor> Your telepathy reaches far beyond the limitations of lesser elan. </Flavor>
		<specific name="Short Description"> Telepathy 10; master and perform telepathic rituals </specific>
		<specific name="Tier"> Paragon </specific>
	        <specific name="type"> Elan Bloodline </specific>
		<rules>		
			<grant name="ID_INTERNAL_INTERNAL_BLOODLINE" type="Internal"/>
			<grant name="ID_INTERNAL_INTERNAL_ELAN_BLOODLINE" type="Internal"/>
</rules>
The range of your telepathy increases to 10 and ignores blocking terrain to determine line of effect. You master and can perform the Sending, Telepathic Bond, and Far Sending rituals as if you had the Ritual Caster feat. You ignore the component cost of the Sending ritual and once per day, you can ignore the component cost of Telepathic Bond or Far Sending.
	</RulesElement>

